var book = {
	"name": "Ezra",
	"numChapters": 10,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12018A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12018A\"></sup>Now in the first year of Cyrus king of Persia, in order to fulfill the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> by the mouth of Jeremiah, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> stirred up the spirit of Cyrus king of Persia, so that he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12018B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12018B\"></sup>sent a proclamation throughout all his kingdom, and also <i>put it</i> in writing, saying:",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Thus says Cyrus king of Persia, ‘The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of heaven, has given me all the kingdoms of the earth and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12019C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12019C\"></sup>He has appointed me to build Him a house in Jerusalem, which is in Judah.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Whoever there is among you of all His people, may his God be with him! Let him go up to Jerusalem which is in Judah and rebuild the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12020D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12020D\"></sup>He is the God who is in Jerusalem.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Every survivor, at whatever place he may live, let the men of that place support him with silver and gold, with goods and cattle, together with a freewill offering for the house of God which is in Jerusalem.’”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then the heads of fathers’ <i>households</i> of Judah and Benjamin and the priests and the Levites arose, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12022E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12022E\"></sup>even everyone whose spirit God had stirred to go up and rebuild the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> which is in Jerusalem.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>All those about them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12023F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12023F\"></sup>encouraged them with articles of silver, with gold, with goods, with cattle and with valuables, aside from all that was given as a freewill offering.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12024G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12024G\"></sup>Also King Cyrus brought out the articles of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12024H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12024H\"></sup>which Nebuchadnezzar had carried away from Jerusalem and put in the house of his gods;",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>and Cyrus, king of Persia, had them brought out by the hand of Mithredath the treasurer, and he counted them out to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12025I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12025I\"></sup>Sheshbazzar, the prince of Judah.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Now this <i>was</i> their number: 30 <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12026J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12026J\"></sup>gold dishes, 1,000 silver dishes, 29 duplicates;",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>30 gold bowls, 410 silver bowls of a second <i>kind and</i> 1,000 other articles.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>All the articles of gold and silver <i>numbered</i> 5,400. Sheshbazzar brought them all up with the exiles who went up from Babylon to Jerusalem."
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12029A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12029A\"></sup>Now these are the people of the province who came up out of the captivity of the exiles whom Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon had carried away to Babylon, and returned to Jerusalem and Judah, each to his city.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>These came with Zerubbabel, Jeshua, Nehemiah, Seraiah, Reelaiah, Mordecai, Bilshan, Mispar, Bigvai, Rehum <i>and</i> Baanah.The number of the men of the people of Israel:",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>the sons of Parosh, 2,172;",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>the sons of Shephatiah, 372;",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12033B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12033B\"></sup>Arah, 775;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12034C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12034C\"></sup>Pahath-moab of the sons of Jeshua <i>and</i> Joab, 2,812;",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>the sons of Elam, 1,254;",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>the sons of Zattu, 945;",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>the sons of Zaccai, 760;",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>the sons of Bani, 642;",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>the sons of Bebai, 623;",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>the sons of Azgad, 1,222;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12041D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12041D\"></sup>Adonikam, 666;",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>the sons of Bigvai, 2,056;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>the sons of Adin, 454;",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>the sons of Ater of Hezekiah, 98;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>the sons of Bezai, 323;",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>the sons of Jorah, 112;",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>the sons of Hashum, 223;",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>the sons of Gibbar, 95;",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>the men of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12049E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12049E\"></sup>Bethlehem, 123;",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>the men of Netophah, 56;",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>the men of Anathoth, 128;",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>the sons of Azmaveth, 42;",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>the sons of Kiriath-arim, Chephirah and Beeroth, 743;",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12054F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12054F\"></sup>Ramah and Geba, 621;",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>the men of Michmas, 122;",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>the men of Bethel and Ai, 223;",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>the sons of Nebo, 52;",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>the sons of Magbish, 156;",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>the sons of the other Elam, 1,254;",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>the sons of Harim, 320;",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>the sons of Lod, Hadid and Ono, 725;",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>the men of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12062G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12062G\"></sup>Jericho, 345;",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>the sons of Senaah, 3,630.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12064H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12064H\"></sup>The priests: the sons of Jedaiah of the house of Jeshua, 973;",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12065I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12065I\"></sup>Immer, 1,052;",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12066J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12066J\"></sup>the sons of Pashhur, 1,247;",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12067K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12067K\"></sup>Harim, 1,017.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>The Levites: the sons of Jeshua and Kadmiel, of the sons of Hodaviah, 74.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>The singers: the sons of Asaph, 128.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>The sons of the gatekeepers: the sons of Shallum, the sons of Ater, the sons of Talmon, the sons of Akkub, the sons of Hatita, the sons of Shobai, in all 139.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12071L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12071L\"></sup>temple servants: the sons of Ziha, the sons of Hasupha, the sons of Tabbaoth,",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>the sons of Keros, the sons of Siaha, the sons of Padon,",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>the sons of Lebanah, the sons of Hagabah, the sons of Akkub,",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>the sons of Hagab, the sons of Shalmai, the sons of Hanan,",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>the sons of Giddel, the sons of Gahar, the sons of Reaiah,",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>the sons of Rezin, the sons of Nekoda, the sons of Gazzam,",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>the sons of Uzza, the sons of Paseah, the sons of Besai,",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>the sons of Asnah, the sons of Meunim, the sons of Nephisim,",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>the sons of Bakbuk, the sons of Hakupha, the sons of Harhur,",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>the sons of Bazluth, the sons of Mehida, the sons of Harsha,",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>the sons of Barkos, the sons of Sisera, the sons of Temah,",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>the sons of Neziah, the sons of Hatipha.",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>The sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12083M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12083M\"></sup>Solomon’s servants: the sons of Sotai, the sons of Hassophereth, the sons of Peruda,",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>the sons of Jaalah, the sons of Darkon, the sons of Giddel,",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup>the sons of Shephatiah, the sons of Hattil, the sons of Pochereth-hazzebaim, the sons of Ami.",
			"58": "<sup class=\"versenum\">58 </sup>All the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12086N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12086N\"></sup>temple servants and the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12086O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12086O\"></sup>Solomon’s servants were 392.",
			"59": "<sup class=\"versenum\">59 </sup>Now these are those who came up from Tel-melah, Tel-harsha, Cherub, Addan <i>and</i> Immer, but they were not able to give evidence of their fathers’ households and their descendants, whether they were of Israel:",
			"60": "<sup class=\"versenum\">60 </sup>the sons of Delaiah, the sons of Tobiah, the sons of Nekoda, 652.",
			"61": "<sup class=\"versenum\">61 </sup>Of the sons of the priests: the sons of Habaiah, the sons of Hakkoz, the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12089P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12089P\"></sup>Barzillai, who took a wife from the daughters of Barzillai the Gileadite, and he was called by their name.",
			"62": "<sup class=\"versenum\">62 </sup>These searched <i>among</i> their ancestral registration, but they could not be located; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12090Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12090Q\"></sup>therefore they were considered unclean <i>and excluded</i> from the priesthood.",
			"63": "<sup class=\"versenum\">63 </sup>The governor said to them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12091R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12091R\"></sup>that they should not eat from the most holy things until a priest stood up with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12091S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12091S\"></sup>Urim and Thummim.",
			"64": "<sup class=\"versenum\">64 </sup>The whole assembly numbered 42,360,",
			"65": "<sup class=\"versenum\">65 </sup>besides their male and female servants who numbered 7,337; and they had 200 <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12093T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12093T\"></sup>singing men and women.",
			"66": "<sup class=\"versenum\">66 </sup>Their horses were 736; their mules, 245;",
			"67": "<sup class=\"versenum\">67 </sup>their camels, 435; <i>their</i> donkeys, 6,720.",
			"68": "<sup class=\"versenum\">68 </sup>Some of the heads of fathers’ <i>households</i>, when they arrived at the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> which is in Jerusalem, offered willingly for the house of God to restore it on its foundation.",
			"69": "<sup class=\"versenum\">69 </sup>According to their ability they gave <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12097U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12097U\"></sup>to the treasury for the work 61,000 gold drachmas and 5,000 silver minas and 100 priestly garments.",
			"70": "<sup class=\"versenum\">70 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12098V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12098V\"></sup>Now the priests and the Levites, some of the people, the singers, the gatekeepers and the temple servants lived in their cities, and all Israel in their cities."
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span>Now when the seventh month came, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12099A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12099A\"></sup>the sons of Israel <i>were</i> in the cities, the people gathered together as one man to Jerusalem.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12100B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12100B\"></sup>Jeshua the son of Jozadak and his brothers the priests, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12100C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12100C\"></sup>Zerubbabel the son <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12100D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12100D\"></sup>of Shealtiel and his brothers arose and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12100E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12100E\"></sup>built the altar of the God of Israel to offer burnt offerings on it, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12100F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12100F\"></sup>as it is written in the law of Moses, the man of God.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So they set up the altar on its foundation, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12101G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12101G\"></sup>they were terrified because of the peoples of the lands; and they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12101H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12101H\"></sup>offered burnt offerings on it to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, burnt offerings morning and evening.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>They celebrated the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12102I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12102I\"></sup>Feast of Booths, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12102J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12102J\"></sup>as it is written, and <i>offered</i> the fixed number of burnt offerings daily, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12102K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12102K\"></sup>according to the ordinance, as each day required;",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and afterward <i>there was</i> a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12103L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12103L\"></sup>continual burnt offering, also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12103M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12103M\"></sup>for the new moons and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12103N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12103N\"></sup>for all the fixed festivals of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that were consecrated, and from everyone who offered a freewill offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>From the first day of the seventh month they began to offer burnt offerings to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, but the foundation of the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had not been laid.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then they gave money to the masons and carpenters, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12105O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12105O\"></sup>food, drink and oil to the Sidonians and to the Tyrians, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12105P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12105P\"></sup>to bring cedar wood from Lebanon to the sea at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12105Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12105Q\"></sup>Joppa, according to the permission they had from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12105R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12105R\"></sup>Cyrus king of Persia.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Now in the second year of their coming to the house of God at Jerusalem in the second month, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12106S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12106S\"></sup>Zerubbabel the son of Shealtiel and Jeshua the son of Jozadak and the rest of their brothers the priests and the Levites, and all who came from the captivity to Jerusalem, began <i>the work</i> and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12106T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12106T\"></sup>appointed the Levites from twenty years and older to oversee the work of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12107U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12107U\"></sup>Jeshua <i>with</i> his sons and brothers stood united <i>with</i> Kadmiel and his sons, the sons of Judah <i>and</i> the sons of Henadad <i>with</i> their sons and brothers the Levites, to oversee the workmen in the temple of God.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now when the builders had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12108V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12108V\"></sup>laid the foundation of the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the priests stood in their apparel with trumpets, and the Levites, the sons of Asaph, with cymbals, to praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12108W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12108W\"></sup>according to the directions of King David of Israel.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12109X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12109X\"></sup>They sang, praising and giving thanks to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <i>saying</i>, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12109Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12109Y\"></sup>For He is good, for His lovingkindness is upon Israel forever.” And all the people shouted with a great shout when they praised the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> because the foundation of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was laid.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Yet many of the priests and Levites and heads of fathers’ <i>households</i>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12110Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12110Z\"></sup>the old men who had seen the first temple, wept with a loud voice when the foundation of this house was laid before their eyes, while many shouted aloud for joy,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>so that the people could not distinguish the sound of the shout of joy from the sound of the weeping of the people, for the people shouted with a loud shout, and the sound was heard far away."
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span>Now when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12112A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12112A\"></sup>the enemies of Judah and Benjamin heard that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12112B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12112B\"></sup>the people of the exile were building a temple to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>they approached Zerubbabel and the heads of fathers’ <i>households</i>, and said to them, “Let us build with you, for we, like you, seek your God; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12113C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12113C\"></sup>and we have been sacrificing to Him since the days of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12113D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12113D\"></sup>Esarhaddon king of Assyria, who brought us up here.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But Zerubbabel and Jeshua and the rest of the heads of fathers’ <i>households</i> of Israel said to them, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12114E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12114E\"></sup>You have nothing in common with us in building a house to our God; but we ourselves will together build to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12114F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12114F\"></sup>as King Cyrus, the king of Persia has commanded us.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12115G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12115G\"></sup>the people of the land discouraged the people of Judah, and frightened them from building,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and hired counselors against them to frustrate their counsel all the days of Cyrus king of Persia, even until the reign of Darius king of Persia.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Now in the reign of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12117H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12117H\"></sup>Ahasuerus, in the beginning of his reign, they wrote an accusation against the inhabitants of Judah and Jerusalem.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And in the days of Artaxerxes, Bishlam, Mithredath, Tabeel and the rest of his colleagues wrote to Artaxerxes king of Persia; and the text of the letter was written in Aramaic and translated <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12118I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12118I\"></sup><i>from</i> Aramaic.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Rehum the commander and Shimshai the scribe wrote a letter against Jerusalem to King Artaxerxes, as follows—",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>then <i>wrote</i> Rehum the commander and Shimshai the scribe and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12120J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12120J\"></sup>the rest of their colleagues, the judges and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12120K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12120K\"></sup>the lesser governors, the officials, the secretaries, the men of Erech, the Babylonians, the men of Susa, that is, the Elamites,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and the rest of the nations which the great and honorable Osnappar deported and settled in the city of Samaria, and in the rest of the region beyond the River. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12121L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12121L\"></sup>Now",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>this is the copy of the letter which they sent to him:“To King Artaxerxes: Your servants, the men in the region beyond the River, and now",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>let it be known to the king that the Jews who came up from you have come to us at Jerusalem; they are rebuilding <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12123M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12123M\"></sup>the rebellious and evil city and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12123N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12123N\"></sup>are finishing the walls and repairing the foundations.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Now let it be known to the king, that if that city is rebuilt and the walls are finished, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12124O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12124O\"></sup>they will not pay tribute, custom or toll, and it will damage the revenue of the kings.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Now because we are in the service of the palace, and it is not fitting for us to see the king’s dishonor, therefore we have sent and informed the king,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>so that a search may be made in the record books of your fathers. And you will discover in the record books and learn that that city is a rebellious city and damaging to kings and provinces, and that they have incited revolt within it in past days; therefore that city was laid waste.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>We inform the king that if that city is rebuilt and the walls finished, as a result you will have no possession in <i>the province</i> beyond the River.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><i>Then</i> the king sent an answer to Rehum the commander, to Shimshai the scribe, and to the rest of their colleagues who live in Samaria and in the rest of <i>the provinces</i> beyond the River: “Peace. And now",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>the document which you sent to us has been <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12129P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12129P\"></sup>translated and read before me.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>A decree has been issued by me, and a search has been made and it has been discovered that that city has risen up against the kings in past days, that rebellion and revolt have been perpetrated in it,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12131Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12131Q\"></sup>that mighty kings have ruled over Jerusalem, governing all <i>the provinces</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12131R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12131R\"></sup>beyond the River, and that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12131S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12131S\"></sup>tribute, custom and toll were paid to them.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So, now issue a decree to make these men stop <i>work</i>, that this city may not be rebuilt until a decree is issued by me.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Beware of being negligent in carrying out this <i>matter</i>; why should damage increase to the detriment of the kings?”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then as soon as the copy of King Artaxerxes’ document was read before Rehum and Shimshai the scribe and their colleagues, they went in haste to Jerusalem to the Jews and stopped them by force of arms.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then work on the house of God in Jerusalem ceased, and it was stopped until the second year of the reign of Darius king of Persia."
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span>When the prophets, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12136A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12136A\"></sup>Haggai the prophet and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12136B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12136B\"></sup>Zechariah the son of Iddo, prophesied to the Jews who were in Judah and Jerusalem in the name of the God of Israel, who was over them,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12137C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12137C\"></sup>Zerubbabel the son of Shealtiel and Jeshua the son of Jozadak arose and began to rebuild the house of God which is in Jerusalem; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12137D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12137D\"></sup>the prophets of God were with them supporting them.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>At that time <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12138E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12138E\"></sup>Tattenai, the governor of <i>the province</i> beyond the River, and Shethar-bozenai and their colleagues came to them and spoke to them thus, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12138F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12138F\"></sup>Who issued you a decree to rebuild this temple and to finish this structure?”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12139G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12139G\"></sup>Then we told them accordingly what the names of the men were who were reconstructing this building.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12140H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12140H\"></sup>the eye of their God was on the elders of the Jews, and they did not stop them until a report could come to Darius, and then a written reply be returned concerning it.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><i>This is</i> the copy of the letter which <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12141I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12141I\"></sup>Tattenai, the governor of <i>the province</i> beyond the River, and Shethar-bozenai and his colleagues <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12141J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12141J\"></sup>the officials, who were beyond the River, sent to Darius the king.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>They sent a report to him in which it was written thus: “To Darius the king, all peace.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Let it be known to the king that we have gone to the province of Judah, to the house of the great God, which is being built with huge stones, and beams are being laid in the walls; and this work is going on with great care and is succeeding in their hands.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then we asked those elders and said to them thus, ‘Who issued you a decree to rebuild this temple and to finish this structure?’",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>We also asked them their names so as to inform you, and that we might write down the names of the men who were at their head.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Thus they answered us, saying, ‘We are the servants of the God of heaven and earth and are rebuilding the temple that was built many years ago, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12146K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12146K\"></sup>which a great king of Israel built and finished.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12147L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12147L\"></sup>because our fathers had provoked the God of heaven to wrath, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12147M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12147M\"></sup>He gave them into the hand of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon, the Chaldean, <i>who</i> destroyed this temple and deported the people to Babylon.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>However, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12148N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12148N\"></sup>in the first year of Cyrus king of Babylon, King Cyrus <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12148O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12148O\"></sup>issued a decree to rebuild this house of God.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12149P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12149P\"></sup>the gold and silver utensils of the house of God which Nebuchadnezzar had taken from the temple in Jerusalem, and brought them to the temple of Babylon, these King Cyrus took from the temple of Babylon and they were given to one <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12149Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12149Q\"></sup>whose name was Sheshbazzar, whom he had appointed governor.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>He said to him, “Take these utensils, go <i>and</i> deposit them in the temple in Jerusalem and let the house of God be rebuilt in its place.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then that Sheshbazzar came <i>and</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12151R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12151R\"></sup>laid the foundations of the house of God in Jerusalem; and from then until now it has been under construction and it is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12151S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12151S\"></sup>not <i>yet</i> completed.’",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“Now if it pleases the king, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12152T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12152T\"></sup>let a search be conducted in the king’s treasure house, which is there in Babylon, if it be that a decree was issued by King Cyrus to rebuild this house of God at Jerusalem; and let the king send to us his decision concerning this <i>matter</i>.”"
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span>Then King Darius issued a decree, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12153A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12153A\"></sup>search was made in the archives, where the treasures were stored in Babylon.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>In Ecbatana in the fortress, which is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12154B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12154B\"></sup>in the province of Media, a scroll was found and there was written in it as follows: “Memorandum—",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12155C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12155C\"></sup>In the first year of King Cyrus, Cyrus the king issued a decree: ‘<i>Concerning</i> the house of God at Jerusalem, let the temple, the place where sacrifices are offered, be rebuilt and let its foundations be retained, its height being 60 cubits and its width 60 cubits;",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12156D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12156D\"></sup>with three layers of huge stones and one layer of timbers. And let the cost be paid from the royal treasury.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Also let <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12157E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12157E\"></sup>the gold and silver utensils of the house of God, which Nebuchadnezzar took from the temple in Jerusalem and brought to Babylon, be returned and brought to their places in the temple in Jerusalem; and you shall put <i>them</i> in the house of God.’",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“Now <i>therefore</i>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12158F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12158F\"></sup>Tattenai, governor of <i>the province</i> beyond the River, Shethar-bozenai and your colleagues, the officials of <i>the provinces</i> beyond the River, keep away from there.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Leave this work on the house of God alone; let the governor of the Jews and the elders of the Jews rebuild this house of God on its site.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Moreover, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12160G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12160G\"></sup>I issue a decree concerning what you are to do for these elders of Judah in the rebuilding of this house of God: the full cost is to be paid to these people from the royal treasury out of the taxes of <i>the provinces</i> beyond the River, and that without delay.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Whatever is needed, both young bulls, rams, and lambs for a burnt offering to the God of heaven, and wheat, salt, wine and anointing oil, as the priests in Jerusalem request, <i>it</i> is to be given to them daily without fail,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>that they may offer acceptable sacrifices to the God of heaven and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12162H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12162H\"></sup>pray for the life of the king and his sons.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And I issued a decree that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12163I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12163I\"></sup>any man who violates this edict, a timber shall be drawn from his house and he shall be impaled on it and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12163J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12163J\"></sup>his house shall be made a refuse heap on account of this.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>May the God who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12164K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12164K\"></sup>has caused His name to dwell there overthrow any king or people who attempts to change <i>it</i>, so as to destroy this house of God in Jerusalem. I, Darius, have issued <i>this</i> decree, let <i>it</i> be carried out with all diligence!”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12165L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12165L\"></sup>Tattenai, the governor of <i>the province</i> beyond the River, Shethar-bozenai and their colleagues carried out <i>the decree</i> with all diligence, just as King Darius had sent.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12166M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12166M\"></sup>the elders of the Jews were successful in building through the prophesying of Haggai the prophet and Zechariah the son of Iddo. And they finished building according to the command of the God of Israel and the decree <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12166N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12166N\"></sup>of Cyrus, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12166O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12166O\"></sup>Darius, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12166P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12166P\"></sup>Artaxerxes king of Persia.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>This temple was completed on the third day of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12167Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12167Q\"></sup>month Adar; it was the sixth year of the reign of King Darius.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And the sons of Israel, the priests, the Levites and the rest of the exiles, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12168R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12168R\"></sup>celebrated the dedication of this house of God with joy.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>They offered for the dedication of this temple of God 100 bulls, 200 rams, 400 lambs, and as a sin offering for all Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12169S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12169S\"></sup>12 male goats, corresponding to the number of the tribes of Israel.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then they appointed the priests to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12170T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12170T\"></sup>their divisions and the Levites in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12170U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12170U\"></sup>their orders for the service of God in Jerusalem, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12170V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12170V\"></sup>as it is written in the book of Moses.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12171W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12171W\"></sup>The exiles observed the Passover on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12171X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12171X\"></sup>the fourteenth of the first month.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12172Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12172Y\"></sup>For the priests and the Levites had purified themselves together; all of them were pure. Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12172Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12172Z\"></sup>they slaughtered the Passover <i>lamb</i> for all the exiles, both for their brothers the priests and for themselves.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The sons of Israel who returned from exile and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12173AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12173AA\"></sup>all those who had separated themselves from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12173AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12173AB\"></sup>the impurity of the nations of the land to <i>join</i> them, to seek the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel, ate <i>the Passover</i>.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12174AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12174AC\"></sup>they observed the Feast of Unleavened Bread seven days with joy, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had caused them to rejoice, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12174AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12174AD\"></sup>had turned the heart of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12174AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12174AE\"></sup>the king of Assyria toward them to encourage them in the work of the house of God, the God of Israel."
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12175A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12175A\"></sup>Now after these things, in the reign of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12175B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12175B\"></sup>Artaxerxes king of Persia, <i>there went up</i> Ezra son of Seraiah, son of Azariah, son of Hilkiah,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>son of Shallum, son of Zadok, son of Ahitub,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>son of Amariah, son of Azariah, son of Meraioth,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>son of Zerahiah, son of Uzzi, son of Bukki,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>son of Abishua, son of Phinehas, son of Eleazar, son of Aaron the chief priest.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>This Ezra went up from Babylon, and he was a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12180C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12180C\"></sup>scribe skilled in the law of Moses, which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel had given; and the king granted him all he requested <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12180D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12180D\"></sup>because the hand of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God <i>was</i> upon him.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12181E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12181E\"></sup>Some of the sons of Israel and some of the priests, the Levites, the singers, the gatekeepers and the temple servants went up to Jerusalem in the seventh year of King Artaxerxes.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He came to Jerusalem in the fifth month, which was in the seventh year of the king.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>For on the first of the first month he began to go up from Babylon; and on the first of the fifth month he came to Jerusalem, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12183F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12183F\"></sup>because the good hand of his God <i>was</i> upon him.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>For Ezra had set his heart to study the law of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and to practice <i>it</i>, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12184G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12184G\"></sup>to teach <i>His</i> statutes and ordinances in Israel.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now this is the copy of the decree which King Artaxerxes gave to Ezra the priest, the scribe, learned in the words of the commandments of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and His statutes to Israel:",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“Artaxerxes, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12186H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12186H\"></sup>king of kings, to Ezra the priest, the scribe of the law of the God of heaven, perfect <i>peace</i>. And now",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12187I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12187I\"></sup>I have issued a decree that any of the people of Israel and their priests and the Levites in my kingdom who are willing to go to Jerusalem, may go with you.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Forasmuch as you are sent by the king and his <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12188J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12188J\"></sup>seven counselors to inquire concerning Judah and Jerusalem according to the law of your God which is in your hand,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>and to bring the silver and gold, which the king and his counselors have freely offered to the God of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12189K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12189K\"></sup>whose dwelling is in Jerusalem,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12190L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12190L\"></sup>all the silver and gold which you find in the whole province of Babylon, along <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12190M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12190M\"></sup>with the freewill offering of the people and of the priests, who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12190N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12190N\"></sup>offered willingly for the house of their God which is in Jerusalem;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>with this money, therefore, you shall diligently buy bulls, rams and lambs, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12191O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12191O\"></sup>with their grain offerings and their drink offerings and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12191P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12191P\"></sup>offer them on the altar of the house of your God which is in Jerusalem.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Whatever seems good to you and to your brothers to do with the rest of the silver and gold, you may do according to the will of your God.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Also the utensils which are given to you for the service of the house of your God, deliver in full before the God of Jerusalem.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The rest of the needs for the house of your God, for which you may have occasion to provide, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12194Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12194Q\"></sup>provide <i>for it</i> from the royal treasury.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“I, even I, King Artaxerxes, issue a decree to all the treasurers who are <i>in the provinces</i> beyond the River, that whatever Ezra the priest, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12195R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12195R\"></sup>the scribe of the law of the God of heaven, may require of you, it shall be done diligently,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><i>even</i> up to 100 talents of silver, 100 kors of wheat, 100 baths of wine, 100 baths of oil, and salt as needed.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Whatever is commanded by the God of heaven, let it be done with zeal for the house of the God of heaven, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12197S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12197S\"></sup>so that there will not be wrath against the kingdom of the king and his sons.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>We also inform you that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12198T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12198T\"></sup>it is not allowed to impose tax, tribute or toll <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12198U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12198U\"></sup><i>on</i> any of the priests, Levites, singers, doorkeepers, Nethinim or servants of this house of God.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“You, Ezra, according to the wisdom of your God which is in your hand, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12199V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12199V\"></sup>appoint magistrates and judges that they may judge all the people who are in <i>the province</i> beyond the River, <i>even</i> all those who know the laws of your God; and you may <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12199W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12199W\"></sup>teach anyone who is ignorant <i>of them</i>.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12200X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12200X\"></sup>Whoever will not observe the law of your God and the law of the king, let judgment be executed upon him strictly, whether for death or for banishment or for confiscation of goods or for imprisonment.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Blessed be the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of our fathers, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12201Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12201Y\"></sup>who has put <i>such a thing</i> as this in the king’s heart, to adorn the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> which is in Jerusalem,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12202Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12202Z\"></sup>has extended lovingkindness to me before the king and his counselors and before all the king’s mighty princes. Thus I was strengthened according to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12202AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12202AA\"></sup>the hand of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God upon me, and I gathered leading men from Israel to go up with me."
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span>Now these are the heads of their fathers’ <i>households</i> and the genealogical enrollment of those who went up with me from Babylon in the reign of King Artaxerxes:",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>of the sons of Phinehas, Gershom; of the sons of Ithamar, Daniel; of the sons of David, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12204A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12204A\"></sup>Hattush;",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>of the sons of Shecaniah <i>who was</i> of the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12205B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12205B\"></sup>Parosh, Zechariah and with him 150 males <i>who were in</i> the genealogical list;",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>of the sons of Pahath-moab, Eliehoenai the son of Zerahiah and 200 males with him;",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>of the sons of Zattu, Shecaniah, the son of Jahaziel and 300 males with him;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and of the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12208C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12208C\"></sup>Adin, Ebed the son of Jonathan and 50 males with him;",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and of the sons of Elam, Jeshaiah the son of Athaliah and 70 males with him;",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>and of the sons of Shephatiah, Zebadiah the son of Michael and 80 males with him;",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>of the sons of Joab, Obadiah the son of Jehiel and 218 males with him;",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and of the sons of Bani, Shelomith, the son of Josiphiah and 160 males with him;",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and of the sons of Bebai, Zechariah the son of Bebai and 28 males with him;",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>and of the sons of Azgad, Johanan the son of Hakkatan and 110 males with him;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and of the sons of Adonikam, the last ones, these being their names, Eliphelet, Jeuel and Shemaiah, and 60 males with them;",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and of the sons of Bigvai, Uthai and Zabbud, and 70 males with them.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Now I assembled them at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12217D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12217D\"></sup>the river that runs to Ahava, where we camped for three days; and when I observed the people and the priests, I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12217E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12217E\"></sup>did not find any Levites there.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So I sent for Eliezer, Ariel, Shemaiah, Elnathan, Jarib, Elnathan, Nathan, Zechariah and Meshullam, leading men, and for Joiarib and Elnathan, teachers.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>I sent them to Iddo the leading man at the place Casiphia; and I told them what to say to Iddo <i>and</i> his brothers, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12219F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12219F\"></sup>the temple servants at the place Casiphia, <i>that is</i>, to bring ministers to us for the house of our God.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12220G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12220G\"></sup>According to the good hand of our God upon us they brought us a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12220H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12220H\"></sup>man of insight of the sons of Mahli, the son of Levi, the son of Israel, namely Sherebiah, and his sons and brothers, 18 men;",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>and Hashabiah and Jeshaiah of the sons of Merari, with his brothers and their sons, 20 men;",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>and 220 of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12222I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12222I\"></sup>the temple servants, whom David and the princes had given for the service of the Levites, all of them designated by name.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then I proclaimed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12223J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12223J\"></sup>a fast there at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12223K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12223K\"></sup>the river of Ahava, that we might <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12223L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12223L\"></sup>humble ourselves before our God to seek from Him a safe journey for us, our little ones, and all our possessions.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>For I was ashamed to request from the king troops and horsemen to protect us from the enemy on the way, because we had said to the king, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12224M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12224M\"></sup>The hand of our God is favorably disposed to all those who seek Him, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12224N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12224N\"></sup>His power and His anger are against all those who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12224O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12224O\"></sup>forsake Him.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So we fasted and sought our God concerning this <i>matter</i>, and He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12225P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12225P\"></sup>listened to our entreaty.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then I set apart twelve of the leading priests, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12226Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12226Q\"></sup>Sherebiah, Hashabiah, and with them ten of their brothers;",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>and I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12227R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12227R\"></sup>weighed out to them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12227S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12227S\"></sup>the silver, the gold and the utensils, the offering for the house of our God which the king and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12227T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12227T\"></sup>his counselors and his princes and all Israel present <i>there</i> had offered.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12228U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12228U\"></sup>Thus I weighed into their hands 650 talents of silver, and silver utensils <i>worth</i> 100 talents, <i>and</i> 100 gold talents,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>and 20 gold bowls <i>worth</i> 1,000 darics, and two utensils of fine shiny bronze, precious as gold.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then I said to them, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12230V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12230V\"></sup>You are holy to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12230W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12230W\"></sup>utensils are holy; and the silver and the gold are a freewill offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of your fathers.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Watch and keep <i>them</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12231X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12231X\"></sup>until you weigh <i>them</i> before the leading priests, the Levites and the heads of the fathers’ <i>households</i> of Israel at Jerusalem, <i>in</i> the chambers of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>So the priests and the Levites <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12232Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12232Y\"></sup>accepted the weighed out silver and gold and the utensils, to bring <i>them</i> to Jerusalem to the house of our God.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then we journeyed from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12233Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12233Z\"></sup>the river Ahava on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12233AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12233AA\"></sup>the twelfth of the first month to go to Jerusalem; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12233AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12233AB\"></sup>the hand of our God was over us, and He delivered us from the hand of the enemy and the ambushes by the way.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12234AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12234AC\"></sup>Thus we came to Jerusalem and remained there three days.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>On the fourth day the silver and the gold and the utensils <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12235AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12235AD\"></sup>were weighed out in the house of our God into the hand of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12235AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12235AE\"></sup>Meremoth the son of Uriah the priest, and with him <i>was</i> Eleazar the son of Phinehas; and with them <i>were</i> the Levites, Jozabad the son of Jeshua and Noadiah the son of Binnui.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Everything <i>was</i> numbered and weighed, and all the weight was recorded at that time.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12237AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12237AF\"></sup>The exiles who had come from the captivity offered burnt offerings to the God of Israel: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12237AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12237AG\"></sup>12 bulls for all Israel, 96 rams, 77 lambs, 12 male goats for a sin offering, all as a burnt offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12238AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12238AH\"></sup>they delivered the king’s edicts to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12238AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12238AI\"></sup>the king’s satraps and to the governors <i>in the provinces</i> beyond the River, and they supported the people and the house of God."
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span>Now when these things had been completed, the princes approached me, saying, “The people of Israel and the priests and the Levites have not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12239A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12239A\"></sup>separated themselves from the peoples of the lands, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12239B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12239B\"></sup>according to their abominations, <i>those</i> of the Canaanites, the Hittites, the Perizzites, the Jebusites, the Ammonites, the Moabites, the Egyptians and the Amorites.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12240C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12240C\"></sup>they have taken some of their daughters <i>as wives</i> for themselves and for their sons, so that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12240D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12240D\"></sup>the holy race has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12240E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12240E\"></sup>intermingled with the peoples of the lands; indeed, the hands of the princes and the rulers have been foremost in this unfaithfulness.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>When I heard about this matter, I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12241F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12241F\"></sup>tore my garment and my robe, and pulled some of the hair from my head and my beard, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12241G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12241G\"></sup>sat down appalled.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12242H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12242H\"></sup>everyone who trembled at the words of the God of Israel on account of the unfaithfulness of the exiles gathered to me, and I sat appalled until <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12242I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12242I\"></sup>the evening offering.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But at the evening offering I arose from my humiliation, even with my garment and my robe torn, and I fell on my knees and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12243J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12243J\"></sup>stretched out my hands to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and I said, “O my God, I am ashamed and embarrassed to lift up my face to You, my God, for our iniquities have risen above our heads and our <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12244K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12244K\"></sup>guilt has grown even to the heavens.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12245L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12245L\"></sup>Since the days of our fathers to this day we <i>have been</i> in great guilt, and on account of our iniquities we, our kings <i>and</i> our priests have been given into the hand of the kings of the lands, to the sword, to captivity and to plunder and to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12245M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12245M\"></sup>open shame, as <i>it is</i> this day.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But now for a brief moment grace has been <i>shown</i> from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12246N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12246N\"></sup>to leave us an escaped remnant and to give us a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12246O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12246O\"></sup>peg in His holy place, that our God may <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12246P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12246P\"></sup>enlighten our eyes and grant us a little reviving in our bondage.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12247Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12247Q\"></sup>For we are slaves; yet in our bondage our God has not forsaken us, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12247R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12247R\"></sup>has extended lovingkindness to us in the sight of the kings of Persia, to give us reviving to raise up the house of our God, to restore its ruins and to give us a wall in Judah and Jerusalem.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“Now, our God, what shall we say after this? For we have forsaken Your commandments,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>which You have commanded by Your servants the prophets, saying, ‘The land which you are entering to possess is an unclean land with the uncleanness of the peoples of the lands, with their abominations which have filled it from end to end <i>and</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12249S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12249S\"></sup>with their impurity.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>So now do not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12250T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12250T\"></sup>give your daughters to their sons nor take their daughters to your sons, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12250U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12250U\"></sup>never seek their peace or their prosperity, that you may be strong and eat the good <i>things</i> of the land and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12250V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12250V\"></sup>leave <i>it</i> as an inheritance to your sons forever.’",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>After all that has come upon us for our evil deeds and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12251W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12251W\"></sup>our great guilt, since You our God have requited <i>us</i> less than our iniquities <i>deserve</i>, and have given us <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12251X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12251X\"></sup>an escaped remnant as this,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12252Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12252Y\"></sup>shall we again break Your commandments and intermarry with the peoples who commit these abominations? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12252Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12252Z\"></sup>Would You not be angry with us to the point of destruction, until there is no remnant nor any who escape?",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12253AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12253AA\"></sup>You are righteous, for we have been left an escaped remnant, as <i>it is</i> this day; behold, we are before You in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12253AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12253AB\"></sup>our guilt, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12253AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12253AC\"></sup>no one can stand before You because of this.”"
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12254A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12254A\"></sup>while Ezra was praying and making confession, weeping and prostrating himself <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12254B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12254B\"></sup>before the house of God, a very large assembly, men, women and children, gathered to him from Israel; for the people wept bitterly.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Shecaniah the son of Jehiel, one of the sons of Elam, said to Ezra, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12255C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12255C\"></sup>We have been unfaithful to our God and have married foreign women from the peoples of the land; yet now there is hope for Israel in spite of this.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12256D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12256D\"></sup>let us make a covenant with our God to put away all the wives and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12256E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12256E\"></sup>their children, according to the counsel of my lord and of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12256F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12256F\"></sup>those who tremble at the commandment of our God; and let it be done <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12256G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12256G\"></sup>according to the law.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Arise! For <i>this</i> matter is your responsibility, but we will be with you; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12257H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12257H\"></sup>be courageous and act.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then Ezra rose and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12258I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12258I\"></sup>made the leading priests, the Levites and all Israel, take oath that they would do according to this proposal; so they took the oath.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then Ezra <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12259J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12259J\"></sup>rose from before the house of God and went into the chamber of Jehohanan the son of Eliashib. Although he went there, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12259K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12259K\"></sup>he did not eat bread nor drink water, for he was mourning over the unfaithfulness of the exiles.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>They made a proclamation throughout Judah and Jerusalem to all the exiles, that they should assemble at Jerusalem,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>and that whoever would not come within three days, according to the counsel of the leaders and the elders, all his possessions should be forfeited and he himself excluded from the assembly of the exiles.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So all the men of Judah and Benjamin assembled at Jerusalem within the three days. It was the ninth month on the twentieth of the month, and all the people sat in the open square <i>before</i> the house of God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12262L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12262L\"></sup>trembling because of this matter and the heavy rain.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then Ezra the priest stood up and said to them, “You have been unfaithful and have married foreign wives adding to the guilt of Israel.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now therefore, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12264M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12264M\"></sup>make confession to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of your fathers and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12264N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12264N\"></sup>do His will; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12264O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12264O\"></sup>separate yourselves from the peoples of the land and from the foreign wives.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then all the assembly replied with a loud voice, “That’s right! As you have said, so it is our duty to do.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But there are many people; it is the rainy season and we are not able to stand in the open. Nor <i>can</i> the task <i>be done</i> in one or two days, for we have transgressed greatly in this matter.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Let our leaders represent the whole assembly and let all those in our cities who have married foreign wives come at appointed times, together with the elders and judges of each city, until the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12267P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12267P\"></sup>fierce anger of our God on account of this matter is turned away from us.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Only Jonathan the son of Asahel and Jahzeiah the son of Tikvah opposed this, with Meshullam and Shabbethai the Levite supporting them.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But the exiles did so. And Ezra the priest selected men <i>who were</i> heads of fathers’ <i>households</i> for <i>each of</i> their father’s households, all of them by name. So they convened on the first day of the tenth month to investigate the matter.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>They finished <i>investigating</i> all the men who had married foreign wives by the first day of the first month.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Among the sons of the priests who had married foreign wives were found of the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12271Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12271Q\"></sup>Jeshua the son of Jozadak, and his brothers: Maaseiah, Eliezer, Jarib and Gedaliah.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>They pledged to put away their wives, and being guilty, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12272R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12272R\"></sup><i>they offered</i> a ram of the flock for their offense.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Of the sons of Immer <i>there were</i> Hanani and Zebadiah;",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>and of the sons of Harim: Maaseiah, Elijah, Shemaiah, Jehiel and Uzziah;",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>and of the sons of Pashhur: Elioenai, Maaseiah, Ishmael, Nethanel, Jozabad and Elasah.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Of Levites <i>there were</i> Jozabad, Shimei, Kelaiah (that is, Kelita), Pethahiah, Judah and Eliezer.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Of the singers <i>there was</i> Eliashib; and of the gatekeepers: Shallum, Telem and Uri.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Of Israel, of the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12278S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12278S\"></sup>Parosh <i>there were</i> Ramiah, Izziah, Malchijah, Mijamin, Eleazar, Malchijah and Benaiah;",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>and of the sons of Elam: Mattaniah, Zechariah, Jehiel, Abdi, Jeremoth and Elijah;",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>and of the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12280T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12280T\"></sup>Zattu: Elioenai, Eliashib, Mattaniah, Jeremoth, Zabad and Aziza;",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>and of the sons of Bebai: Jehohanan, Hananiah, Zabbai <i>and</i> Athlai;",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>and of the sons of Bani: Meshullam, Malluch and Adaiah, Jashub, Sheal <i>and</i> Jeremoth;",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>and of the sons of Pahath-moab: Adna, Chelal, Benaiah, Maaseiah, Mattaniah, Bezalel, Binnui and Manasseh;",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>and <i>of</i> the sons of Harim: Eliezer, Isshijah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12284U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12284U\"></sup>Malchijah, Shemaiah, Shimeon,",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Benjamin, Malluch <i>and</i> Shemariah;",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>of the sons of Hashum: Mattenai, Mattattah, Zabad, Eliphelet, Jeremai, Manasseh <i>and</i> Shimei;",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>of the sons of Bani: Maadai, Amram, Uel,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Benaiah, Bedeiah, Cheluhi,",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Vaniah, Meremoth, Eliashib,",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Mattaniah, Mattenai, Jaasu,",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Bani, Binnui, Shimei,",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Shelemiah, Nathan, Adaiah,",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Machnadebai, Shashai, Sharai,",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Azarel, Shelemiah, Shemariah,",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Shallum, Amariah <i>and</i> Joseph.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Of the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12296V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12296V\"></sup>Nebo <i>there were</i> Jeiel, Mattithiah, Zabad, Zebina, Jaddai, Joel <i>and</i> Benaiah.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>All these had married <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-12297W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-12297W\"></sup>foreign wives, and some of them had wives <i>by whom</i> they had children."
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;